# xray — example environment file.
#
# Copy to `.env` and fill in. `.env` is gitignored and MUST NEVER be COPYied
# into the Docker image — secrets enter at `docker run` time only.
# See .claude/rules/public-repo.md §2.

# --- Server ---
# Port the Bun process listens on inside the container.
PORT=8080
# Bind address. The validated default (loaded from env.ts) is `127.0.0.1` — safe
# for `bun src/server/main.ts` on a host. Inside Docker (via `compose.yaml`)
# the container's compose file overrides this to `0.0.0.0`; do NOT bake
# `HOST=0.0.0.0` into a shell-level `.env` or you'll expose the
# unauthenticated API to your LAN.
# HOST=0.0.0.0
# Directory holding the SQLite store file (`xray.db`). In Docker this is the
# mounted volume; locally with `bun src/server/main.ts` set it to `./data`.
XRAY_DATA_DIR=/data
# Optional override for the audio root. Defaults to `$XRAY_DATA_DIR/audio`.
# Per-turn and full-replay audio files live here, indexed by replay id.
# XRAY_AUDIO_ROOT=/data/audio

# --- Dev compose ---
# Run dev containers as the host user so files written into the bind-mounted
# repo (./:/app) are owned by you, not root. Without these, a compromised dev
# dependency could write to .git/hooks, package.json, etc. with root perms.
#   export UID GID                 # bash/zsh
UID=1000
GID=1000
